PLAIN-LANGUAGE SUMMARY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

• If you want to reuse the code (lift the HTML/CSS/JS into another project,
  build derivative tools, fork the implementation): MIT terms apply — keep
  the copyright notice and you are otherwise free.

• If you want to use the game itself (republish the rules, translate them,
  use the calibrated lists in your own product, recreate the lab, write a
  derived game): CC BY 4.0 terms apply — credit Elad Dafni and link this
  license.

• If you use both together (e.g., clone the whole repo, host it as-is, or
  produce a derived edition): comply with both licenses for their respective
  parts.

Questions or commercial licensing inquiries: contact the author.


